<subSubSection id="C3485ED6094FB211EC95FF6723894B4C" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D094FB211EC95FF6722494AD0" blockId="27.[151,1437,187,861]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis id="B926D14F094FB211EC95FF6721294AFC" bold="true" box="[151,290,187,213]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Etymology:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE094FB211ED2AFF67218A4AFC" authorityName="Bloch &amp; Schneider" authorityYear="1801" box="[296,385,187,213]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Eleotridae" genus="Eleotris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F094FB211ED2AFF67218A4AFC" box="[296,385,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Eleotris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: the name of a Nile fish, eleotris; 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE094FB211EEFEFF6723944AFC" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1853" box="[764,927,187,213]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Eleotridae" genus="Eleotris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acanthopomus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F094FB211EEFEFF6723944AFC" box="[764,927,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">acanthopomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: refers to the downward-pointing spine at the posterior margin of the preoperculum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D094FB211ECC5FEDE22854B34" blockId="27.[151,1437,187,861]" box="[199,654,258,285]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis id="B926D14F094FB211ECC5FEDE218C4B34" bold="true" box="[199,391,258,285]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Common name:</emphasis>
Spine-cheek Gudgeon.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D094FB211ECC5FEFB23894B4C" blockId="27.[151,1437,187,861]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis id="B926D14F094FB211ECC5FEFB21454B68" bold="true" box="[199,334,295,321]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Taxonomy:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE094FB211ED55FEFB22564B68" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1853" box="[343,605,295,321]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Eleotridae" genus="Eleotris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acanthopomus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F094FB211ED55FEFB22564B68" box="[343,605,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Eleotris acanthopomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Bleeker [P.] 1853:275 [Natuurkundig Tijdschrift voor Nederlandsch Indië v. 4 (no. 2)] from Western 
<collectingRegion id="4996C3BF094FB211EEA0FE9723094B4C" box="[674,770,331,357]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD094FB211EF0FFE9723754B4C" box="[781,894,331,357]" name="Indonesia" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3485ED6094FB211ECC5FEB3215148E4" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D094FB211ECC5FEB322524BA0" blockId="27.[151,1437,187,861]" box="[199,601,366,393]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">
<materialsCitation id="3B3A0700094FB211ECC5FEB322524BA0" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3766721351" box="[199,601,366,393]" collectionCode="RMNH" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" specimenCode="RMNH 25934" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<emphasis id="B926D14F094FB211ECC5FEB321A24BA1" bold="true" box="[199,425,366,393]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">
<typeStatus id="54E9B3FF094FB211ECC5FEB3213F4BA0" box="[199,308,367,393]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Holotype</typeStatus>
(unique):
</emphasis>
<specimenCode id="DBF4A526094FB211EDB3FEB3225D4BA0" box="[433,598,366,393]" collectionCode="RMNH" country="Netherlands" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34992" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34992" name="National Museum of Natural History, Naturalis" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" type="Museum">RMNH 25934</specimenCode>
.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D094FB211ECC5FE4E25204848" blockId="27.[151,1437,187,861]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis id="B926D14F094FB211ECC5FE4E21AA4B85" bold="true" box="[199,417,402,428]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Short description:</emphasis>
D 
<collectionCode id="ED439598094FB211EDC1FE4F21E94B84" box="[451,482,403,429]" country="Norway" name="Mykotektet, National Veterinary Institute" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">VI</collectionCode>
–I, 8; A I, 8; Pt 16; P2 I, 5; LR 51; TR 16; Pred. S 41; P-V 3/1 II II 1/8; 
<collectionCode id="ED439598094FB211E905FE4F25104B84" box="[1287,1307,403,429]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
10+15=25. The species of this genus have a downward-pointing spine at the posterior margin of the preoperculum, which is covered with skin. The species are distinguished by the differences in the sensory papillae. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5276DE094FB211E89BFE0725974BDC" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1853" box="[1177,1436,475,501]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Eleotridae" genus="Eleotris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acanthopomus">
<emphasis id="B926D14F094FB211E89BFE0725974BDC" box="[1177,1436,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Eleotris acanthopomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 5 transverse rows of papillae below the eyes. The 2nd and 4th transverse rows extend downwards beyond the longitudinal row below them, but the 3rd and 5th do not. Two longitudinal rows on the operculum do not touch at the posterior ends. Inhabits mainly brackish water. Takes up life at the bottom before it reaches 
<quantity id="4CAAA0B8094FB211E8C6FD9B24F04848" box="[1220,1275,583,609]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
SL.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D094FB211ECC5FDB6215148E4" blockId="27.[151,1437,187,861]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis id="B926D14F094FB211ECC5FDB621CE48AD" bold="true" box="[199,453,618,644]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">General distribution:</emphasis>
Indo-West Pacific: 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD094FB211EEA2FDB7230148AC" box="[672,778,619,645]" name="Comoros" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Comoros</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD094FB211EF16FDB7238448AC" box="[788,911,619,645]" name="Seychelles" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Seychelles</collectingCountry>
; 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD094FB211EF9BFDB7240D48AC" box="[921,1030,619,645]" name="Indonesia" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
east to 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD094FB211E85BFDB724DC48AC" box="[1113,1239,619,645]" name="Micronesia" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Micronesia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD094FB211E90EFDB720D84880" name="French Polynesia" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">French Polynesia</collectingCountry>
, north to 
<collectingRegion id="4996C3BF094FB211ED4BFD53221D4880" box="[329,534,655,681]" country="Japan" name="Ibaraki" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Ibaraki Prefecture</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD094FB211EE2AFD5322664880" box="[552,621,655,681]" name="Japan" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Japan</collectingCountry>
), south to northern 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD094FB211EF56FD5323B04880" box="[852,955,655,681]" name="Australia" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">Australia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3454DCD094FB211EFFBFD5324A64880" box="[1017,1197,655,681]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
. Habitat: freshwater, brackish, marine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3485ED6094FB211ECC5FD0A24DF4974" pageId="27" pageNumber="478" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BED0D5D094FB211ECC5FD0A23B8493C" blockId="27.[151,1437,187,861]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">
<emphasis id="B926D14F094FB211ECC5FD0A21DF48D9" bold="true" box="[199,468,726,752]" pageId="27" pageNumber="478">
Distribution in 
